CHAT.comment: Teaching. Mother and Child sit on living+room floor. Mother first teaches Child to string beads on a shoelace. Then she teaches him to sort black and white buttons into separate piles. Child's speech is fairly intelligible. Child's nickname is Ra.

u.a: gives correct end of string to Child .
attitude shifts , losing patience , no longer trying to teach him .
holds Child's hands , tries to help him .
doesn't pull , just holds bead , wants Mother to pull .
gives Child correct end to pull .
sits back with her own string and bead .
pulls crying Child on her lap .
